                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17441205-4-off23 t17441205-4-crimeloc27"></join>. Last Saturday morning there was an iron rail lost from his chapel, which was fixed to the stone-work; the stone was broke, and the iron rail was taken out.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17441205-4-person64">
                  James 
                  Leaver 
               <interp inst="t17441205-4-person64" type="surname" value="Leaver"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17441205-4-person64" type="given" value="James"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17441205-4-person64" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a watchman. I saw that bar in the range about five minutes before I missed it - About three o'clock last Saturday morning, I saw the Prisoner go off with something in his hand which looked like a bar. I cried out, stop thief, and followed him to the Horse Guards, and heard him throw something down.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17441205-4-person65">
                  Henry 
                  Nicholls 
               <interp inst="t17441205-4-person65" type="surname" value="Nicholls"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17441205-4-person65" type="given" value="Henry"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17441205-4-person65" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was centry at the Pay Office. On Saturday morning last, about half an hour after two, the Prisoner came running along as fast as he could: hearing the watch call out, I stopped him at Scotland-Yard Gate, and kept him till the watchman came up. The Prisoner was charged by the Watchman for stealing an iron bar, but he said he knew nothing of the matter; the bar was drawn out from under the gate, and a hammer was found in the street, a little way off the gate. <rs id="t17441205-4-verdict28" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17441205-4-verdict28" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17441205-4-verdict28" type="verdictSubcategory" value="theftunder1s"></interp>
               Guilty 10 d.
            </rs>
               </p>
